
QoS Classes, and How They Get That Way
=================================================

1. If you specify the same request and limit for
   both CPU and Memory, you get Guaranteed Service.

   That's because you are most predictable. You 
   know exactly what you need to run. and you know 
   you will not need any more. 

   Schedulers *like* predictability.


2. If you know the minimum you need, but you might 
   need more, then you get the next rung down.
   We will give you what you need, and maybe we will
   be able to "burst" you higher. And maybe not.


3. If you walk in the door with no clue what you need
   we will give you whatever scraps may be left over 
   by the grownups.





